<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-12-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                        <head>No. 8.<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Earl of
                                    Derby</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to">Layard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                        Office</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-12-19"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 19,
                                    1874</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I transmit to you herewith a copy of a
                            note from the Spanish minister at this Court,<note n="*" xml:id="d279fn1">No. 6.</note> inclosing a check for £6,700, on
                            account of the claims of the families of the British subjects executed
                            at Santiago de Cuba, in November, 1873, for participation in the
                            Virginius affair.</p>
                        <p>I also inclose a copy of the answer which I have returned to Señor
                                Comyn.<note n="†" xml:id="d279fn2">No. 7.</note></p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>DERBY.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>